  "text": "Module 1 of the ENVE methodology consists of four steps as follows: In this module ( Fig. 1 ), genome-wide segmental LogRatios for each of the (N !)/(2 * (N − 2) !) random normal-normal combinations are calculated using read depth comparison and circular binary segmentation [CITATION_1] . For each sample pair being compared, each target region within the exome is divided into non-overlapping 100-bp windows.",
